---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
	title='Editorial Policy'
	description='How QuBrite uses AI, verifies technical claims, and discloses commercial relationships.'
>
	<main class='mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 prose prose-stone dark:prose-invert'>
		<h1 class='text-4xl font-bold not-prose'>Editorial Policy</h1>
		<p>
			QuBrite focuses on practical, technical, and commercially relevant coverage of AI web
			building, automation systems, cyber labs, privacy tech, hardware, and business systems. Every
			piece should help a reader ship, secure, or operate something—not fill a keyword quota.
		</p>

		<h2>AI-assisted drafting</h2>
		<p>
			We use AI tools for research, outlining, and first drafts. AI does not publish on its own: a
			human editor reviews structure, claims, links, and tone before anything goes live. We follow{' '}
			<a href='https://developers.google.com/search/docs/fundamentals/creating-helpful-content'
				>Google&apos;s helpful content guidance</a
			>—people-first, experience-backed, not scaled filler.
		</p>

		<h2>Fact-checking and updates</h2>
		<p>
			Technical claims are checked against primary sources (official docs, vendor security advisories,
			government guidance) where possible. Software versions, pricing, and product availability
			change; we set <code>updatedDate</code> in frontmatter when guidance materially changes and
			refresh internal links when related articles ship.
		</p>

		<h2>Affiliate and commercial relationships</h2>
		<p>
			Some hardware and software links may be affiliate links. Affiliate relationships do not
			determine what we recommend—we document trade-offs and alternatives. See our{' '}
			<a href='/affiliate-disclosure/'>affiliate disclosure</a> for details.
		</p>

		<h2>Who we are</h2>
		<p>
			Learn more about the desk on the <a href='/about/'>about page</a>. Questions or corrections:{' '}
			<a href='/contact/'>contact us</a>.
		</p>
	</main>
</BaseLayout>
